Other factors
-------------

1.  The side with the best tactician gets a free round of attacks
    at the start of battle.

    If both sides have no unit skilled in Tactics, or if the tacticians 
    are equally matched, then neither side will gain a free round of
    attacks.

    The best tactician for each side will be chosen, regardless of
    where in the stack he may be.

2.  Knights and elite guard receive a -25 penalty to both their
    attack and defense ratings when fighting in a swampy province.

3.  In wind, the attack rating for crossbowmen, archers and
    elite archers is halved.  In rain, the attack rating for
    missile fighters is reduced to their defense rating.

4.  When battling on the ocean, siege engines are not used.

    Knights and elite guard receive a -25 penalty to both their
    attack and defense ratings.

    If the galley is fitted with a ram, it will behave like a
    battering ram on land.

